	<div class="mw-indicators">
	</div>
	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading mw-first-heading"><span class="mw-page-title-main">Big-game fishing</span></h1>
	<div id="bodyContent" class="vector-body">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
		<div id="contentSub"></div>
		<div id="contentSub2"></div>
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#searchInput">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content mw-content-ltr" lang="en" dir="ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><div class="shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style="display:none">Offshore sportfishing targeting large fish such as tuna or marlin</div>
<div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Striped_Blue_Marlin.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/Striped_Blue_Marlin.jpg/300px-Striped_Blue_Marlin.jpg" decoding="async" width="300" height="200" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/Striped_Blue_Marlin.jpg/450px-Striped_Blue_Marlin.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/Striped_Blue_Marlin.jpg/600px-Striped_Blue_Marlin.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1024" data-file-height="683" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Striped_Blue_Marlin.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Seven-foot (two-meter) Indo-Pacific blue marlin (<i><a href="/wiki/Makaira_mazara" class="mw-redirect" title="Makaira mazara">Makaira mazara</a></i>). This big-game fish was caught near <a href="/wiki/Cabo_San_Lucas" title="Cabo San Lucas">Cabo San Lucas</a>, on the Pacific coast of Mexico.</div></div></div>
<p><b>Big-game fishing</b>, also known as <b>offshore sportfishing</b>, <b>offshore gamefishing</b> or <b>blue-water fishing</b>, is a form of <a href="/wiki/Recreational_fishing" title="Recreational fishing">recreational fishing</a> targeting large <a href="/wiki/Game_fish" title="Game fish">game fish</a>, usually done on a large <a href="/wiki/Body_of_water" title="Body of water">body of water</a> such as the <a href="/wiki/Ocean" title="Ocean">ocean</a>.
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc" role="navigation" aria-labelledby="mw-toc-heading"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2 id="mw-toc-heading">Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
